SIMPLE: whereat
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Whereat
<hw>Where*at"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>adv.</pos>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>At which; upon which; whereupon; -- used
relatively.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>They vote; <qex>whereat</qex> his speech he thus renews.</q>
<rj><qau>Milton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q><qex>Whereat</qex> he was no less angry and ashamed than desirous
to obey Zelmane.</q> <rj><qau>Sir P. Sidney.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>At what; -- used interrogatively; as,
<xex>whereat</xex> are you offended?</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Whereby</ent>⟦br⟧
